<h1>Outer Planets</h1>
<p>The outer planets are Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune. These planets are much larger and farther from the Sun.</p>

<h2>Jupiter</h2>
<p>Jupiter is the largest planet in the solar system and is famous for the Great Red Spot.</p>

<h2>Saturn</h2>
<p>Saturn is well known for its beautiful ring system.</p>

<h2>Uranus</h2>
<p>Uranus rotates on its side, which makes it very unusual compared to other planets.</p>

<h2>Neptune</h2>
<p>Neptune is a cold, distant planet with very strong winds.</p>

